- and -chains that remain disulﬁde linked, referred to as cleaved, two-chain mature HPs. The two-chain mature HPs are abundant plasma
glycoproteins and are composed of their - and -subunits covalently associated by three disulﬁde bonds in which the carbohydrate groups are
exclusively linked to the -chain. [Modiﬁed from Camarca et al. (29).]
