EGFR and, therefore, to cause TJ disassembly only in its
uncleaved form. Several G protein-coupled receptors
(GPCR), including PAR2, transactivate EGFR (164). Zonu-
lin prokaryotic counterpart Zot active peptide FCIGRL
(AT1002) has structural similarities with PAR2-activating
peptide
(AP),
